Package com.samju.hospital.service

Class RadiologyService

java.lang.Object
com.samju.hospital.service.RadiologyService
@Service public class RadiologyService extends Object
The RadiologyService class provides business logic for managing Radiology entities in the hospital management system. It is annotated with Service to indicate that it is a Spring service and should be automatically detected and registered in the application context.

The service relies on the RadiologyRepository for basic CRUD operations on radiology records. Additionally, it utilizes the MongoTemplate for more complex MongoDB-specific operations.

Methods in this service include:

  • invalid @link 
    #createScan(String, String, String, String, String)
    : Create a new radiology record and associate it with a patient.

Usage example: 

 
 public class SomeController {
     RadiologyService radiologyService;

     // Some method that uses the service
     void someMethod() {
         Radiology newScanResult = radiologyService.createScan("Imaging Center", "555-123-4567", "X-ray Images", "Detailed Report", "P789");
         // Perform operations with the created radiology record
     }
 }

    • createScan

      public Radiology createScan(String fullName, String phoneNumber, org.springframework.web.multipart.MultipartFile file, String reports, String registrationNumber) throws IOException
      Create a new radiology record and associate it with a patient identified by the registration number.
      Parameters:
      fullName - The full name of the radiology center conducting the scan.
      phoneNumber - The contact phone number of the radiology center.
      file - The images produced by the radiology scan.
      reports - The detailed reports or findings from the radiology scan.
      Returns:
      The created radiology record.
      Throws:
      IOException
